# Implementation Plan - WhatsApp Cloud API Bulk Sender App (Path A)

We will create a separate, dedicated application in a new directory `c:\Users\Admin\Desktop\whatsapp api sender` that uses the official WhatsApp Business Cloud API. This version will be lightweight, will not run Puppeteer (no heavy browser overhead), will run with zero risk of phone number bans, and will support real-time delivery status via Meta Webhooks.

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Requirements for Meta Cloud API:**
> To use the new app, you will need to:
> 1. Set up a Meta Developer Account, a WhatsApp Business app, and obtain:
>    * **Access Token** (Permanent)
>    * **Phone Number ID**
>    * **WhatsApp Business Account ID (WABA ID)**
> 2. Submit and get approval for your message templates in the **Meta Business Manager** (usually approved in minutes).
> 3. Provide a public URL (e.g. via ngrok or your hosting provider) to configure the Webhook callback URL in the Meta Dashboard if you want to track live "Delivered" and "Read" receipts.

