## Proposed Changes

We will create the new project at `c:\Users\Admin\Desktop\whatsapp api sender`.

### 1. New Project Files

#### [NEW] [package.json](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/whatsapp%20api%20sender/package.json)
Initializes dependencies for the API app, removing heavy browser automation dependencies:
- **Keep:** `express`, `socket.io`, `csv-parser`, `xlsx`, `multer`
- **Add:** `axios` (for REST API calls)
- **Remove:** `puppeteer-extra`, `puppeteer-extra-plugin-stealth`, `whatsapp-web.js`, `qrcode`, `qrcode-terminal`

#### [NEW] [server.js](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/whatsapp%20api%20sender/server.js)
Backend server rewritten to interface with Meta Cloud API instead of Puppeteer:
- Load API credentials from a local file `settings.json`.
- Implement a campaign loop that maps CSV rows to Meta template parameters and fires `axios.post` to `https://graph.facebook.com/v20.0/<PhoneNumberID>/messages`.
- Implement a `/webhook` GET/POST endpoint to verify and receive webhook events (Delivered, Read, Sent, Failed) from Meta and forward them to the UI using socket.io.
- Maintain campaign checkpoints, history, and status logging without running standard client browsers.

#### [NEW] [public/index.html](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/whatsapp%20api%20sender/public/index.html)
Modified front-end dashboard:
- Replace the QR code modal and browser links with an API Credential Settings card.
- Redesign the Campaign Creator tab: Replace raw textareas with:
  - **Template Name** input field (e.g., `marketing_broadcast`).
  - **Language Code** selection/input (e.g., `en`).
  - **Variable mapping** input: Define which CSV columns to map to template variables (e.g., mapping column `Name` to `{{1}}` and `Offer` to `{{2}}`).
- Retain reports, logs, and history layouts.

#### [NEW] [public/script.js](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/whatsapp%20api%20sender/public/script.js)
Refactored front-end controller:
- Connect to socket.io and load/save settings containing API credentials.
- Handle template naming and variable mapping submission.
- Render incoming webhook-based status changes (Delivered/Read/Failed) immediately.

#### [NEW] [public/style.css](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/whatsapp%20api%20sender/public/style.css)
Copy of the modern premium CSS stylesheet to preserve the visual appearance of the dashboard.

